{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":36262,"record_hash":"sha256:72c9704564add63e0678d5b5cce11adb27a0b5cd5fa36ac0a0dd1d58b66a30ef","timestamp":"2026-05-12T08:44:30.101Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"status\":{\"[REDACTED:entropy]\":{\"completed\":\"Read the three docs; no files edited.\\n\\n| Approach | Best For | Shortcut | Tradeoff |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Explicit “Attach session” action | Both handoff and review sharing | Session card has `Attach to branch/change/PR` and `Continue from this session` | Most trustworthy, but users can forget |\\n| Commit/amend confirmation | Review sharing | Commit UI shows recent sessions as suggested context; user checks what applies | Adds a small step, but uses the moment with real change evidence |\\n| PR/share prep picker | Review sharing | PR view has “Related agent sessions” with search, recency, preview, add/remove | Great post-hoc correction; less useful before PR exists |\\n| Visible “active session for this work” | Session handoff, early planning | User pins one active session; GitButler offers it when continuing elsewhere | Can go stale, so needs a badge, expiry, and easy clear |\\n| Suggest-only inference | Both, secondary | File/time/model signals rank sessions but never silently attach | Helps discovery without creating false provenance |\\n\\n**Recommended direction**\\n\\nUse a layered, explicit-first model:\\n\\n1. Keep capture project-scoped only.\\n2. Add an explicit session picker/attach flow as the primary association mechanism.\\n3. In commit/amend and PR creation flows, show suggested sessions, but require confirmation.\\n4. Store relationships as coarse many-to-many `gitbutler:agent-sessions` references to session keys.\\n5. Treat branch/PR views as unions of related sessions, not owners of transcript data.\\n\\nThe product shortcut is to make confirmation feel lightweight: recent sessions, transcript preview, “attach all from today,” and “continue from this session.” The important line: inference may rank or preselect, but should not silently write durable relationships.\"}},\"timed_out\":false}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-12T08:44:30.101Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}